HEADWORD: A mensa et thoro
<hw>A men"sa et tho"ro</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[L., from board and
bed.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A kind of divorce which does not
dissolve the marriage bond, but merely authorizes a separate life of the
husband and wife.</def> <rj><au>Abbott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ament</ent>⟦br⟧
